HEADWORD: Cologne
<hw>Co*logne"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Originally made in
<etsep>Cologne</etsep>, the French name of K⟦oum⟧ln, a city in
Germany.]</ety> <def>A perfumed liquid, composed of alcohol and certain
aromatic oils, used in the toilet; -- called also <altname>cologne
water</altname> and <altname>eau de cologne</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

